<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Horsing Around Allowed in Pool Swimming pools have long been a hallmark 
of Southern California, so it's probably not that surprising that the horses at 
Hollywood Park race track in Inglewood have one too. It's a little bigger than 
the ones found in most back yards -- 14 feet deep and about 75 feet across -- 
and it features an entrance ramp because horses aren't too agile on steps or 
diving boards. Tony Monseto, top, leads Ayaabi, an 8-year-old Thoroughbred 
around pool, while above, worker helps Press Star, a 4-year-old filly into the 
water. Cheryl Dougherty, who manages the pool for the track, said it is used in 
the Thoroughbreds' training regimen. MEL MELCON 
</P>
