<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: L.A. SUES MISSION HILLS ADULT BOOKSTORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several months of undercover investigation has led to a lawsuit against a 
Mission Hills adult bookstore. 
</P>
<P>
A suit filed Thursday by the city attorney's office in Los Angeles Superior 
Court named the Talk of the Valley Bookstore, 15452 Devonshire St., and its 
owners, Frederick Alfano and Michael H. Colella. It charged them with allowing 
lewd conduct and solicitation for lewd conduct in and near booths used by 
patrons to view pornographic films. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation was started by undercover police officers in January. It led 
to 14 arrests for lewd conduct and solicitation, said Mike Qualls, a spokesman 
for the city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
He said the office plans to seek a pretrial court order imposing strict rules 
on the bookstore's operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
