in the sixth inning that tied the score, 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
In another District 20 game: 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 11, Foothill Valley 9 -- Tom Gibson had a three-run home run in the 
third and a grand slam in the fourth to keep Reseda's playoff hopes alive at 
Casey Stengel Field in Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
Chad Calabria was four for four and scored twice for Reseda (11-10). Despite 
allowing 14 hits and nine earned runs, Mario Valencia (3-3) pitched a complete 
game. 
</P>
<P>
