<P>
PUBLIC BREAST-FEEDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a breast-feeding mother, I was appalled at Chasen's statement regarding 
breast-feeding policies at its establishment -- "We don't get those kind of 
people here" ("Restaurants Rethink Their Nursing Policies in the Wake of 
Lawsuit," by Laurie Ochoa, June 28). 
</P>
<P>
I am a college-educated professional and a mother of two (I even read the 
newspaper) and have (gasp!) nursed both of my babies in premier restaurant 
dining rooms. 
</P>
<P>
I don't know what "kind of people" frequent Chasen's, but you can be sure it 
won't be me -- breast-feeding or otherwise. 
</P>
<P>
SUE MAZZARINO 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
