<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENING; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DEDICATED DIGGERS AND PLANTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
To conserve moisture in container plantings, be sure to mulch. 
</P>
<P>
Keep faded blooms picked off your annuals so they will continue blooming and 
filling the summer garden with color. 
</P>
<P>
For interesting foliage color, consider planting the multicolored coleus or 
gray-foliaged dusty miller, artemisia, parrots beak and others found at a local 
nursery. 
</P>
<P>
For some red-hot color in the hot summer garden, plant salvia. 
</P>
