<P>
FLOOD TOLL RISES TO 800 DEAD, 3,000 INJURED IN CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The casualty toll from flooding in China's Sichuan province rose to more than 
800 dead and 3,000 injured Friday as soldiers and paramilitary police joined 
local authorities in rescue efforts, local officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Provincial radio in the capital, Chengdu, reported that the floods have 
affected 20 of the province's 22 cities and prefectures. 
</P>
<P>
The province had already been hit by severe hailstorms this spring, but a flood 
control official said this month's rains "have posed the most severe disaster 
in the last eight years." 
</P>
