<HEADLINE>
<P>
'NEW KIDS ON THE BLOCK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To all you complaining groupies who whined about Chris Willman's insightful and 
perceptive article about the New Kids on the Block, congratulations. You have 
now proved that this group is truly a joke. If you think that thoughtless 
lyrics whined by a group of pubescent teens (who can't seem to find a real 
image) is music, well, wake up. 
</P>
<P>
Although I found your letters shallow and lacking insight, I do agree with you 
on one point: The group does not sound black. To say that it did would be a 
horrible insult to great musicians of the past and present such as the Four 
Tops, Chuck Berry and, more recently, Living Colour. 
</P>
<P>
Screaming groupies ought to stop drooling over Donnie's cute little "itsy-bitsy 
ponytail" and open their ears. I am certain they'd find that the music is not 
only unskillfully made but also quite annoying. 
</P>
<P>
JASON GREENSPAN 
</P>
<P>
