<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three East German soccer players who defected from their team in Sweden have 
arrived in West Germany, according to the Bild newspaper. The three reported to 
the West German consulate in Goteborg Wednesday and were put on board a boat 
that took them to the West German port of Kiel. Bild printed a photograph of 
the three walking away from the ship. 
</P>
