<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Based on erroneous information from old company publications, Friday's obituary 
of Richard G. Adams, former secretary and general counsel for the Times Mirror 
Co., said that he had joined the company in 1930, instead of 1931, and retired 
in 1960, instead of 1966. Also, he attended the University of Colorado and not 
the University of Oklahoma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
