<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LAGUNA NIGUEL; 
</P>
<P>
DEADLINE FOR COUNCIL CANDIDATES IS AUG. 11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The registrar of voters office announced that 5 p.m. on Aug. 11 is the filing 
deadline for Laguna Niguel residents seeking to file as candidates for a 
proposed city council. 
</P>
<P>
Proposed cityhood for Laguna Niguel will be on the ballot in that area on Nov. 
7. In addition to the cityhood referendum, the ballot will have the names of 
candidates seeking the five city council positions. Those five obtaining the 
top vote among the candidates will be elected. They will take office only if a 
majority of residents vote for cityhood. 
</P>
<P>
Nominating petitions for the office of city council may be obtained beginning 
Monday at the registrar of voters office, 1300 S. Grand Ave., Santa Ana. A 
person seeking to run for the council must be a registered voter living within 
the limits of the proposed city of Laguna Niguel. Additionally, a candidate 
must obtain the signatures of 20 to 30 registered voters in that area, and the 
completed petition must be turned into the registrar's office by Aug. 11. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for filing arguments with the registrar for or against Laguna 
Niguel cityhood is 5 p.m. on Aug. 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
