<HEADLINE>
<P>
GENE WOJCIECHOWSKI: DO ANGELS HAVE ALL THE ANSWERS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Gene Wojciechowski 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fifty-three questions to ponder (one for each victory) as the Angels attempt 
the unlikely: a second-half as good as the first. 
</P>
<P>
1) Is this the sequel to "Damn Yankees?" 
</P>
<P>
2) Was Minnesota Twins Manager Tom Kelly serious when he said the Angels were 
the team to beat in the American League West? 
</P>
<P>
3) Has Kelly been reading too many of Gary Gaetti's batting gloves? 
</P>
<P>
4) If American League Manager Tony La Russa needed a left-hander to pitch to 
Von Hayes in the All-Star game, why didn't he use Angel Chuck Finley rather 
than Milwaukee's Dan Plesac? 
</P>
<P>
5) What's more important: complete games or keeping reliever Bryan Harvey 
sharp? 
</P>
<P>
6) There hasn't been an injury to a member of the Angel starting rotation yet, 
has there? 
</P>
<P>
7) When does the Doug Rader Temper Tantrum Watch end? 
</P>
<P>
8) Why do we get the feeling that the Aug. 21-Sept. 3 trip (Kansas City, Texas, 
Boston and New York) will make or break the Angels? 
</P>
<P>
9) Is 1990 the year some major league team hires the other Lachemann (Hint: 
Marcel) as its manager? 
</P>
<P>
10) How long can the Angels succeed with Wally Joyner as their cleanup hitter? 
</P>
<P>
11) What's more annoying at Angel games: beach balls, video instructions on 
when to clap or the sound of breaking glass every time a foul ball falls into 
the crowd? 
</P>
<P>
12) Do you think Nolan Ryan regrets signing with the Texas Rangers? 
</P>
<P>
13) If the Angels don't fade like watercolors, does that mean Mike Port earns 
Executive of the Year honors? 
</P>
<P>
14) Will all those who said Jim Abbott wasn't ready for the majors please stand 
up? 
</P>
<P>
15) Is this the place where I apologize for saying that Bert Blyleven wouldn't 
make a difference? 
</P>
<P>
16) If Rader can have his contract extended halfway through the season, why 
can't Blyleven, whose agreement ends at the end of the year? 
</P>
<P>
17) Is it too late to find a true leadoff hitter? 
</P>
<P>
18) Will Skippy the Lobster be voted an honorary playoff share should the 
Angels make it that far? 
</P>
<P>
19) Why won't Port say the Angels went after Rickey Henderson? 
</P>
<P>
20) Whatever happened to Mark McLemore? 
</P>
<P>
21) Just a thought, but couldn't the curators of the Angels Hall of Fame bend 
the rules a bit to include the jersey of Mr. Jimmie Reese, a keepsake if there 
has ever been one? 
</P>
<P>
22) At what point will Harvey's lack of consistent work catch up with the 
Angels? 
</P>
<P>
23) Now that Bo Jackson has snapped a bat over his head, what will Chili Davis 
do next in response? 
</P>
<P>
24) Does Mike Witt finally have his act together? 
</P>
<P>
25) Can the Angels possibly end the season first in home runs and earned-run 
average? 
</P>
<P>
26) Will shortstop Dick Schofield's dismal batting average ever see the light 
of the .240s? 
</P>
<P>
27) Can the Angels afford another losing streak like their first, when they 
dropped 11 out of 14? 
</P>
<P>
28) Will reliever Greg Minton be able to give Rader 30 more appearances this 
season? 
</P>
<P>
29) Does Tony Armas actually lead the team in batting average? 
</P>
<P>
30) How is it possible that Jack Howell has nine more homers than Joyner? 
</P>
<P>
31) What happens if the Rangers complete a rumored deal that has All-Star 
designated hitter Harold Baines leaving Chicago for Texas? 
</P>
<P>
32) Did you know that the Angels led the division at the All-Star break in 
1979, 1982 and 1986? And that in each of those three years they ended up 
winning the AL West? 
</P>
<P>
33) Did you know that none of that means a single thing in 1989? 
</P>
<P>
34) Do you think Bruce Hurst regrets signing with the San Diego Padres? 
</P>
<P>
