<HEADLINE>
<P>
INVESTMENT FIRM BUYS NETCOM, MAKER OF COMPUTER WORKSTATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES STROUSE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phoenix Group, a Newport Beach investment company headed by entrepreneur 
Charles Missler, said Friday that it has purchased Netcom Research Inc., a 
Fountain Valley maker of computer workstations. 
</P>
<P>
The current value of the purchase is less than $100,000, but the sellers could 
receive as much as $1 million depending on the company's future performance, 
said Netcom spokesman Charles Harrocks. 
</P>
<P>
Harrocks also said Netcom will hire eight new employees in the next five months 
and that present management will remain. 
</P>
<P>
Phoenix will attempt to combine Netcom's technology with telecommunications 
equipment made by Resdel Engineering Corp., an Irvine subsidiary of Resdel 
Industries, which is mostly owned by Phoenix. Resdel is a maker of 
anti-submarine warfare communications equipment. CHARLES STROUSE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
PHOENIX GROUP; ACQUISITIONS; NETCOM RESEARCH INC 
</P>
